12/01/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The UN has allocated 186,000 euros to flooded northern regions and has sent teams to monitor the situation. The UN office in Geneva said on Monday (January 11th) more food and clothes will be sent to those in the hardest hit areas. 
The Serb community in Kosovo sent the fledgling nationâ€™s first shipment of overseas aid. In all, more than 1,000 jackets will be delivered, according to Serb leader Slobodan Petrovic. Kosovo has assisted neighbouring Albania financially, sent a specialised Security Force unit, and has opened some of its towns to evacuees. (Ora News, Top Channel, Klan, Balkan Web - 11/01/10)
